            <li><strong>Mixed origins:</strong> Documents from Egypt (requiring MOFA attestation), UAE Arabic documents, and certified copies</li>
            <li><strong>Volume:</strong> 12 separate items, each requiring different handling</li>
            <li><strong>Attestation requirement:</strong> Egyptian documents needed same-day MOFA processing</li>
            <li><strong>Physical delivery:</strong> Complete package needed for next morning</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>Our Approach</h2>
          <p>We structured the work into three parallel tracks:</p>

          <div class="approach-grid">
            <div class="approach-card">
              <span class="approach-icon">üî¥</span>
              <h3>Track 1: Egyptian Documents</h3>
              <p>Marriage certificate, birth certificates, educational documents, police clearance. These required MOJ translation AND MOFA attestation.</p>
              <p class="approach-note">Priority: Submitted to MOFA by 4 PM for same-day collection</p>
            </div>

            <div class="approach-card">
              <span class="approach-icon">üü°</span>
              <h3>Track 2: UAE Arabic Documents</h3>
              <p>Salary certificate, employment contract, tenancy contract, medical fitness. Standard translation without attestation.</p>
              <p class="approach-note">Completed by 6 PM</p>
            </div>

            <div class="approach-card">
              <span class="approach-icon">üü¢</span>
              <h3>Track 3: Certified Copies</h3>
              <p>Passport copies, Emirates ID, bank statement. Required certified translation and notarization.</p>
              <p class="approach-note">Completed by 9 PM</p>
            </div>
          </div>

